    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2019-03-04</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2020-01-23T16:34:41Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Phair Pricing Act of </b><b>2019</b></p> <p>This bill requires that certain negotiated prices for covered drugs under the Medicare prescription drug benefit be disclosed at the point-of-sale.</p> <p>Specifically, negotiated prices offered under a prescription drug plan (PDP) must be disclosed at the point-of-sale; the disclosed price must include specified adjustments, payments, and fees that are negotiated with the pharmacy (e.g., dispensing fees) by the PDP sponsor or pharmacy benefit manager. </p> <p>Additionally, the Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services must establish certain quality measures for PDP sponsors to use when determining incentive payments and adjustments (e.g., performance payments) to pharmacies.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
